<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hatch3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hatch,</orth> vb. 1) tr. to brood, to disclose by sitting on: <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 33</bibl>. Metaphorically: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.211" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 2, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 60</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to be sat on, to be disclosed by incubation: <cit><quote>why should cuckoos h. in sparrows' nests,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 849" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 849</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>